d to exist on {{date|2009-07-31}} by a decision of the [[Supreme Court of Pakistan]] following Constitution Petition No. 09 and 08 of 2009.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dawn.com/news/889917 |title=Text of Supreme Court judgment |publisher=Pakistan Herald Publication (Pvt.) Ltd |date=2009-08-01 |accessdate=2019-12-22}}</ref>\n\nThe Court was re-established by the [[Islamabad High Court Act, 2010]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.senate.gov.pk/uploads/documents/1363148367_361.pdf |title=The Gazette of Pakistan |date=2010-08-02 |website=Senate of Pakistan |accessdate=2019-12-22}}</ref> following the [[Eighteenth Amendment to the Constitution of Pakistan#Changes to the Constitution|18th Amendment to the Constitution of Pakistan]]. President [[Asif Ali Zardari]] administered the Oath to the first Chief Justice, [[Hameedur Rahman|Iqbal Hameed ur Rahman]] on {{date|2011-01-03}} at the [[Governor's House (Karachi)]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aaj.tv/english/national/ihc-chief-justice-to-take-oath-today/ |title=IHC Chief Justice to take oath today |date=2011-01-03 |publisher= AAJ News |accessdate=2019-12-22}}</ref>\n\n== Justices ==\nThe Islamabad High Court is headed by a Chief Justice. The bench consists of six Justices and additional judges. The mandatory retirement age of the Chief Justice and Justices is 62 years. The Additional Judges were initially appointed for one year. After that their services could either be extended or they could be confirmed or they were retired. The current composition of the High Court is as follows:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!No.\n! Name\n! Appointed\n! Retirement Date\n! Appointed From\n! Comments\n|-\n|1\n|[[Athar Minallah]]\n|{{date|2014-06-17}}\n|{{date|2023-12-12}}\n|Khyber Pakhtunkhwa\n|Appointed as Additional Judge on {{date|2014-06-17}},<ref name=\"9OF2009\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.supremecourt.gov.pk/web/user_files/File/CONST.P.9OF2009.pdf|title=Supreme Court Decision Constitution Petition No. 09 and 08 of 2009|ac